name: Anna Bond
bio:
Mother of 5. Artist & designer. 
Co-founder & chief creative officer @riflepaperco

social_posts.post_text: The greatest gift I could receive this holiday season already arrived: our beautiful girl, Marion. I thought I’d share a few personal family moments from the last few weeks. 💕

Merry Christmas from us to you ❤️🎄

photo by @lironerelco
The colors of Bramble Garden wallpaper 🌼🌿🌸🌹(back when we were reviewing final colors at @york_wallcoverings offices)
All the pretty colors in the NYC @riflepaperco office 💕🌼🌿💙
All the pretty details on our new Curio Sketchbook 🔎🪲
The @riflepaperco shop has never looked more beautiful! Thank you for bringing all our florals to life @velvetandtwine 💕 If only it could stay like this forever.. #riflepaperco
Today in my studio 🌼
Happy Easter 🐇 🌸🥚 #rifleeasteregg #riflepaperco

I’m coming for you Wichita, Kansas! I’m so excited to visit one of Rifle Paper Co.’s best retailers, @loveofcharacter on Sunday, April 30th from 12-2pm at their Bradley Fair location. Stop by, say hello and grab yourself this new (signed) Kansas print. 🌻 (visit @loveofcharacter to RSVP)  #riflepaperco

Happy Mother’s Day from Lisbon ❤️ Seems like a good day to share that we are grateful to be expecting another baby girl in the fall. Nothing brings me more joy than my children and being their mom. And a big Happy Mother’s Day to my mom who is helping to make this trip possible with all our littles at home. 🫶

As a mom of four (soon to be five) I’ve been looking forward to designing a children’s collection. I’m so excited to share our debut @riflepaperco collection with @potterybarnkids & @potterybarnteen. Working on this while I was pregnant with my first daughter was so special and now bringing this beautiful, timeless world of florals to her room feels surreal. Check out my stories for a link to all the bedding, decor, wallpaper and wall art on potterybarnkids.com & potterybarnteen.com (pics of my sweet Marion in her room this morning) 💕

Enjoyed hosting our first dinner party in our new backyard for the @riflepaperco leadership team. I used my favorite linens from @sharland_england, flowers by @velvetandtwine, @riflepaperco ribbon, and an amazing seafood menu for a hot Florida evening by our friend @timlovero 🌸 Looking forward to hosting many more gatherings back here. 🌴
In my studio 🌿
Hand-painted gouache elements to create my new @riflepaperco Blossom print. Filled with 🌻 🐞🌷🍒🌿
Hand-painted art I created for our @riflepaperco x @potterybarnkids 👻🎃💀🍫 collection now available in bedding & adorable PJs 🧡

Good morning 🌞 Can you spot all 5 @riflepaperco things in this corner of her room? I enjoyed using some of our more subdued prints when designing this space for her (and soon to share with her sister) 💗
The softest rugs we make.. Eden Mughal Rose (in moss) & Eden Mughal Garden (in cream) 🌷

hand-painted for my goddaughters as a gift for one of their baptisms that I had the honor of attending in the south of France a couple months ago. Inspired by a painting I saw in Lisbon, Portugal at the beautiful Convento dos Cardaes (photos 2 & 3)
A corner of my studio with this beautiful antique cabinet 💗 Quickly trying to wrap up quite a few painting projects ahead of this baby’s arrival.

Edith Clare Bond arrived late last week and a very swift ~15 min after walking in the hospital. Our second little girl now makes us a family of 7(!). We’re incredibly grateful and both doing well. After 5 babies, I might finally feel like we have the hang of this. However, in light of all the horrific news, it’s also bittersweet. My heart cannot handle the images and stories of unimaginable horror, especially as a mother. We named her Edith in honor of the Jewish Catholic martyr, Saint Edith Stein, which feels even more fitting. 💗
The sleepy, hazy newborn days.. When they get drunk milk tired and sleep curled up on your chest just as they were in the womb 💕
Home 🤎 and a few special things.. vintage splatter bowl, urn by @francespalmer & tole topiary from @getthegusto
Tis the season 🎀 A quick little watercolor sketch
All of our @potterybarnkids x @riflepaperco stockings arrived and they’re so lovely 🥹 It feels very special to have these for our family.
A quick marker & watercolor family tree to frame for my bedroom 🌳

Merry Christmas from my family to yours! (Thank you to Nathan for helping me pull off my one Christmas wish this morning.. a photo with my children 😅) ❤️ I’m so grateful for my family, for having the opportunity to create beautiful things with talented people, and for new & old friends. A few scenes around my home the last couple of days while we spent time together and hosted family. 2023 was a wild one and I look forward to what 2024 has in store.. I hope you all have a wonderful and restful holiday and a very happy New Year.

Obsessed. This beautiful hand-painted wood & ceramic nativity grotto by @tricialowenfielddesign just arrived. Perfect timing to have something special out as we continue to celebrate Christmas as a family through Epiphany. ❤️ Enjoying a slow week taking time off work, nursing colds, and lots of little projects around the house to get things in order as we enter the new year.

2023, you were a wild one…

I had two sweet baby girls within a year and some of our most special family moments. I learned to trust my instincts more and stand up for what I value, celebrated 15 years married to the best husband and father, trips to Portugal and France, New York moments, a very Florida summer, evenings with my closest friends, and one of my busiest years yet designing new things I can’t wait to share. It was one challenging year, but I’m a better person because of it and I suppose that’s what really matters in the end. 

Cheers to 2024! 🥂

It’s a good one. I can’t wait to share our newest collection with you tomorrow, bedding and loungewear in partnership with @thecompanystore! Stock is limited but we will have a number of collections launching throughout the year. So so excited to see this dream finally come to life with the most amazing partner and the best quality 💕🛏 #riflepapercoxthecompanystore
My newest hand-painted pattern, Roses, was inspired by vintage botanical prints and is now available on a handful of lovely new spring products @riflepaperco. Hope you like it! 🌹
New print in the works 🖊
